Module shapes contains one parent class named shape and four derived classes (Rectangle, Circle, Triangle, Trapezoid).

Class Shape:
Two attributes x and y with default value 0.00.
The value of these attributes can be set using functions set_x , set_y.

Class Circle:
Two attributes x and y with default value 0.00.
The value of these attributes can be set using functions set_x , set_y.
Calculates the area of a circle with function area, assuming that radius is x-value.

Class Rectangle:
Two attributes x and y with default value 0.00.
The value of these attributes can be set using functions set_x , set_y.
Calculates the area of a rectangle with function area.

Class Triangle:
Two attributes x and y with default value 0.00.
The value of these attributes can be set using functions set_x , set_y.
Calculates the area of a triangle with function area.


Class Trapezoid:
Three attributes x, y and z with default value 0.00.
The value of these attributes can be set using functions set_x , set_y, set_z.
Calculates the area of a trapezoid with function area.



